cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.NE 

This paper is about building a machine learning model for malware classification based on API call sequences. It involves deep learning techniques such as RNN-based autoencoders and multiple decoders. The paper falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with malware detection and classification. It also involves machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) and software engineering (cs.SE) as it uses deep learning techniques and focuses on building a model for a specific software application. Additionally, it involves neural networks (cs.NE) as it uses RNN-based autoencoders.
